:''Not to be confused with the journal founded in 1841 as [[The Phonetic Journal]]'' {{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Phonetics | cover = [[File:Journal of Phonetics cover.gif]] | editor = Taehong Cho | discipline = [[Phonetics]] | abbreviation = J. Phon. | publisher = [[Elsevier]] | country = | frequency = bimonthly | history = 1973–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.598 | impact-year = 2014 | website = http://www.journals.elsevier.com/journal-of-phonetics/#description | link1 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/00954470 | link1-name = Online access | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 36945983 | LCCN = 73644848 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0095-4470 | eISSN = 1095-8576 }} The '''''Journal of Phonetics''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers topics in [[phonetics]] and [[phonology]]. It was established in 1973 and appears six times a year. It is published by [[Elsevier]] and the current [[editor-in-chief]] is Taehong Cho ([[Hanyang University]]).
According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2014 [[impact factor]] of 1.598, ranked among top 10% in the field of linguistics.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Journal of Phonetics |title=2014 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2016-01-20 |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
== Aims and scope == The Journal of Phonetics publishes papers of an experimental or theoretical nature that deal with phonetic aspects of language and linguistic communication processes. Papers dealing with technological and/or pathological topics, or papers of an interdisciplinary nature are also suitable, provided that linguistic-phonetic principles underlie the work reported. <ref name=aimScope> {{Cite web | title = Journal of Phonetics | work = Aims and scope | publisher = Elsevier | url = http://www.elsevier.com/wps/find/journaldescription.cws_home/622896/description#description | format = | accessdate = 2016-01-20}}</ref>
Regular articles, review articles, and letters to the editor are published. Themed issues are also published, devoted entirely to a specific subject of interest within the field of phonetics.
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in:<ref name=index> {{Cite web | title = Abstracting and Indexing | work = Database indexing | publisher = Elsevier | url = http://www.elsevier.com/wps/find/journalabstracting.cws_home/622896/abstracting#abstracting | format = | accessdate = 2010-12-25 }}</ref>
